### [Daniel Chapter 4](../../../bib/kjv/dan004.htm#001.md)

[Daniel 4:1](../../../bib/kjv/dan004.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">dan 4:1</span></span>

dwell

Nebuchadnezzar, first of the Gentile world-kings in whom the times of
the Gentiles ([Luk 21:24](../../../bib/kjv/luk021.htm#024).md); ([Rev
16:14](../../../bib/kjv/rev016.htm#014).md) began, perfectly comprehended
the universality of the sway committed to him ([Dan
2:37](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#037).md); ([Dan
2:38](../../../bib/kjv/dan002.htm#038).md) as also did Cyrus ([Ezr
1:2](../../../bib/kjv/ezr001.htm#002).md). That they did not actually
subject the known earth to their sway is true, but they might have done
so. The earth lay in their power.

